        <updateDate>2020-02-07T16:59:48Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Clean Slate Act of 2019</b></p> <p>This bill establishes a framework for sealing records related to certain federal criminal offenses.</p> <p>Courts must automatically seal records related to (1) a conviction for simple possession of a controlled substance or for any nonviolent offense involving marijuana, or (2) an arrest for an offense that does not result in a conviction. </p> <p>Additionally, an individual who meets certain criteria may petition to seal records related to a conviction for other nonviolent offenses. </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
